threegpp.milenage.biginteger

Class BigIntegerBuffer

  • java.lang.Object
    • threegpp.milenage.biginteger.BigIntegerBuffer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MilenageBuffer<java.math.BigInteger>

    public class BigIntegerBuffer
extends java.lang.Object
implements MilenageBuffer<java.math.BigInteger>

    MilenageBuffer implementation based on a BigInteger class

    Data buffer to use in calculations of algorithm output blocks.

    The size of buffer assumed as Milenage.BLOCK_LEN_BYTES

    Incapsulates bit/cryptography operations.

    Since:
    06.02.16

      • createIN1

        public static BigIntegerBuffer createIN1(byte[] sqn,
                                         byte[] amf)
        Create buffer IN1 based on contents of SQN and AMF fields. A 128-bit value IN1 is constructed as follows: IN1[0] .. IN1[47] = SQN[0] .. SQN[47] IN1[48] .. IN1[63] = AMF[0] .. AMF[15] IN1[64] .. IN1[111] = SQN[0] .. SQN[47] IN1[112] .. IN1[127] = AMF[0] .. AMF[15]

        Parameters:
        sqn - Array of length Milenage.SQN_LEN_BYTES.
        amf - Array of length Milenage.AMF_LEN_BYTES.
        Returns:
        Result buffer with N1 contents.
